-- China to Raise Minimum Government Wheat Purchase Price in 2011, NDRC Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-12T01:22:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/china-to-raise-minimum-government-wheat-purchase-price-in-2011-ndrc-says.html
China will raise the minimum
government purchasing price for wheat in 2011, the National
Development and Reform Commission said today in a statement on
its website. The government will pay a minimum of 95 yuan for
every 50 kilograms of white wheat, and 93 yuan for red wheat and
mixed wheat, it said. The increases were 5 yuan for white wheat
and 7 yuan for both red and mixed wheat, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
